  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "We've been seeing replicasets going way above the specified `.spec.revisionHistoryLimit`.\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n$ kubectl get rs --selector=component=resque | wc -l\r\n139\r\n$ kubectl get -ojson deploy resque | jq '.spec.revisionHistoryLimit'\r\n5\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe've removed all these excess replica sets, but they keep coming back. We are aware of https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/23597, that's why we set a default for _all_ deployments that we create.\r\n\r\nWe use a CD flow to deploy (multiple times per day), so these leaked RS' are growing quite fast, with the current number already reaching 3K replica sets, even after we cleaned most of them up last week:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n$ kubectl get rs --all-namespaces | wc -l\r\n2607\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe're running on GKE, using Kubernetes version `1.5.1`.",
